		"Name": "Blunderbuss",
		"Details": "The Broadside is a relatively new chassis to the battlefields of the Inner Sphere but Solaris VII never misses an opportunity for innovation. In that vein comes Blunderbuss, a Broadside with a knock-out punch. Built on the same Endo-Steel and TSM skeleton as the regular Broadside, the Blunderbuss swaps the rugged standard engine for an advanced Clan-grade 300-rated XL. It uses this extra free weight to mount a dizzying array of firepower, with a Silver Bullet Gauss Rifle and a Hyper-Assault Gauss Rifle/30 forming the core of the array. An Inner Sphere-spec Gauss Rifle and a Snub-Nose PPC round out the guns, ensuring that the Blunderbuss can one-tap just about anything it can catch. The heat is easily managed by 12 DHS and the design carries enough ammo for most engagements.",
